article.headline: Marshall 81, Morehead St. 80
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Travis Aikens' free throw with 2.4 seconds left helped Marshall beat Morehead State 81-80 Wednesday night. Aikens, who finished with a career-high 23 points, hit one of two free throws to give Marshall (2-4) an 81-77 lead. Brandon Callahan hit a midcourt shot at the buzzer, but Morehead (2-3) was left short. Markel Humphrey scored 17 and Tre Whitted added 10 for the Thundering Herd. Maze Stallworth scored a career-high 21 points to lead Morehead. Quentin Pryor and Callahan finished with 18 and 17 points, respectively, and Cordaryl Ballard had 11. Marshall was ahead 57-39 with 15:08 left in the second half before Morehead State came back to pull to 75-74 on a free throw by Pryor with 2:25 remaining. Marshall was 3-of-6 from the line down the stretch to secure the win. Marshall finished 19-of-28 on free-throw shooting, while Morehead State was just 5-of-9.
